included.description: This degree was completed March of 2012 and includes an emphasis in User-centered Design.

Worked as the sole user researcher for the Prime and Delivery Experience teams, then as part of a team of researchers on the Core Shopping Experience team. While with CSX, I ran the Open Lab program, a user research program for projects without a dedicated research resource.

included.description: Managed user experience research for a variety of clients, from startups to tech giants.
included.title: Researcher

included.description: I assisted in the design of a research repository for content generated by my Lab (Interaction and eXperience Research Lab), then worked on gathering and cataloging research within that group. I also consulted in the development of new exercises to be used in the Futurecasting process.
included.title: Graduate Intern with IXR (Interaction and Experience Research)

included.description: As an intern with the Retail Customer Experience team, I designed, deployed, analyzed and wrote documentation for an online unmoderated study. I also assisted with user research on high-visibility projects focused on both tablets and PCs. In addition to basic study preparation, I was frequently responsible for observation and note-taking during usability sessions using Morae Observer and worked on post-study analysis and reporting.
